## V1 — What we’re shipping

### V1 Definition

V1 is a fully functional financial management tool for households with real-world complexity: multiple people, at least one property, debts, and the need to understand whether their financial life is improving over time. It connects to bank accounts, tracks budgets across three tiers (fixed/flexible/annual), and delivers a monthly review that shows progress since the user started.

### V1 Requirements

Each requirement is numbered. Features cascade from requirements. Claude Code tasks reference requirement numbers.

#### R1. Accurate financial data

The foundation. Every number the user sees must be correct and computed from real transaction data.

|ID  |Requirement                                                             |Status                                  |
|----|------------------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------|
|R1.1|Budget spent amounts are computed from transactions, never stored/cached|🔴 Broken — `Budget.spent` field shows $0|
|R1.2|Fixed expense paid/missed status matches actual transactions            |🔴 Broken — false MISSED flags           |
|R1.3|Amount sign convention enforced at API level (negative=out, positive=in)|🟡 Works in UI, verify API               |
|R1.4|CSV import preserves original data and applies correct signs            |🟢 Working                               |
|R1.5|Plaid import applies correct signs (flip Plaid convention)              |⬜ Not built                             |

#### R2. Bank connectivity

Users connect real bank accounts and transactions flow in automatically.

|ID  |Requirement                                                        |Status     |
|----|-------------------------------------------------------------------|-----------|
|R2.1|User can connect bank accounts via Plaid Link on Accounts page     |⬜ Not built|
|R2.2|Transactions sync daily via cursor-based Plaid API                 |⬜ Not built|
|R2.3|Account balances refresh from Plaid                                |⬜ Not built|
|R2.4|Plaid-imported transactions get correct signs, importSource=“plaid”|⬜ Not built|
|R2.5|Manual accounts remain supported alongside Plaid accounts          |🟢 Working  |

#### R3. Household awareness

The app understands that money belongs to people and properties, not just categories.

|ID  |Requirement                                          |Status     |
|----|-----------------------------------------------------|-----------|
|R3.1|User can create household members (names)            |⬜ Not built|
|R3.2|Every transaction can be tagged to a household member|⬜ Not built|
|R3.3|Spending page supports “By Person” view              |⬜ Not built|
|R3.4|Monthly Review includes per-person spending breakdown|⬜ Not built|

#### R4. Property separation

Transactions are tagged to properties so rental expenses are cleanly separated for tax purposes.

|ID  |Requirement                                             |Status     |
|----|--------------------------------------------------------|-----------|
|R4.1|User can create properties (name, type: Personal/Rental)|⬜ Not built|
|R4.2|Every transaction can be tagged to a property           |⬜ Not built|
|R4.3|Spending page supports “By Property” view/filter        |⬜ Not built|
|R4.4|Transactions page supports property filter              |⬜ Not built|
|R4.5|Year-end: filter by Rental → see all rental expenses    |⬜ Not built|

#### R5. Debt visibility

Users see their complete debt picture: what they owe, what it costs, and whether it’s going down.

|ID  |Requirement                                                               |Status     |
|----|--------------------------------------------------------------------------|-----------|
|R5.1|User can add debts (name, type, balance, rate, minimum payment)           |⬜ Not built|
|R5.2|Debts page shows each debt with principal vs interest breakdown           |⬜ Not built|
|R5.3|Debts page shows total debt summary (total owed, total payments, avg rate)|⬜ Not built|
|R5.4|Debt can link to a property (mortgage → rental)                           |⬜ Not built|
|R5.5|Monthly Review tracks total debt trajectory over time                     |⬜ Not built|

#### R6. Budget tracking (three tiers)

Monthly budgets across Fixed (binary: paid or not), Flexible (progress bars with pace), and Annual (set-aside funding).

|ID  |Requirement                                                                |Status                            |
|----|---------------------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------|
|R6.1|Fixed expenses show paid/missed correctly based on transaction matching    |🔴 Broken                          |
|R6.2|Flexible budgets show accurate spent/limit with $/day remaining            |🔴 Broken (spent=$0)               |
|R6.3|Annual expenses track funding progress with set-aside calculations         |🟢 Working                         |
|R6.4|Annual Plan supports apply-cash and link-transaction funding               |🟢 Working                         |
|R6.5|Auto-Fund All distributes True Remaining to annual expenses                |🟢 Working                         |
|R6.6|True Remaining = income − fixed − annual set-aside, shown as primary metric|🟡 Calculated but not hero position|

#### R7. Monthly Review (progress tracking)

A periodic review that shows trajectory, not just a snapshot. This is what makes Oversikt different.

|ID  |Requirement                                                                                 |Status                                 |
