## V2 — What comes after

### V2 Definition

V2 adds the intelligence and tax layers. Oversikt goes from “shows you what’s true” to “helps you optimize.” Property tagging becomes Schedule E mapping. Debt visibility becomes payoff strategy modeling. Household tagging becomes multi-user with separate logins.

### V2 Requirements (scope only — not specified in detail yet)

|ID   |Requirement                |V2 scope                                                                              |
|-----|---------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|R10.1|Tax system                 |Schedule E line mapping, IRS category crosswalk, deduction strategies, form generation|
|R10.2|Spending benchmarks        |BLS Consumer Expenditure Survey data, “you spend X% more than average”                |
|R10.3|Debt payoff modeling       |Avalanche vs. snowball, “what if” scenarios, refinance comparison                     |
|R10.4|Multi-user household       |Separate logins, permissions, shared views, settlement tracking                       |
|R10.5|Contextual AI on every page|Inline observations (rule-based → AI), cached daily                                   |
|R10.6|Share/export Monthly Review|Image or PDF generation for sharing progress                                          |
|R10.7|Smart auto-tagging         |AI suggests person/property assignments based on merchant patterns                    |
|R10.8|Onboarding wizard          |Guided setup for new users (currently requires manual config)                         |
|R10.9|Depreciation tracking      |Rental property improvement capitalization vs. expense                                |

